<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-10T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-10T04:00:00-05:00" n="1058" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1058">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">760d.61/234: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-10T11:00:00+02:00">October 10,
                                1939—11 a.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received October 10—7:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>232. Press today reports departure for Moscow last night of Minister
                        Paasikivi as special envoy accompanied by Colonel Paasonen the
                            President’s<note n="35" xml:id="d1058fn35">Kyösti Kailio.</note> senior
                            <hi rend="italic">aide-de-camp</hi> as military expert and Mr. Nykopp of
                        the Foreign Office as secretary. Evidence of military preparations on
                        extensive scale increasingly apparent.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>